commit.message: Reworked readmes
Moved to top-level
dsl files for new locales
change NO to NB
change dbl1no to dbl1nb within files

added Kirghiz locale. Thanks to Ilyas Bakirov. Closes patch #2693556.
also, renamed dbl1no.dsl to dbl1nb.dsl

Renamed cvstools dir to buildtools, and replaced all
references to "cvstools" in makefiles and elsewhere
with "buildtools".
Do not display footnote numbers in table of contents. (bug #532560)

Have collateindex.pl handle alphabets with non-ASCII characters.
(SF patch #1208502)

Change refentry element to produce a simple-page-sequence as root object
when the refentry element is at the root of the document.

Ignore `subtitle' children of `book' and `part', since subtitles are
already processed in the construction rule for the root element.

Added style specs in `$section-title$' for `(section subtitle)'.  See
Bug 814331.  Changed the value of the variable `sect' in the
construction rule for `subtitle', so that subtitles indeed have a
smaller font size.

Added style specs in `$section-title$' for `(section subtitle)'.
See Bug 814331.

Eliminate spurious footnotes in the index if %footnote-ulinks% is true.
(bug #423815)
plain-text release notes, added target to make
RELEASE-NOTES.html and freshmeat targets added
ignore RELEASE-NOTES.txt
initial add
Version 1.79 released.
ignore RELEASE-NOTES.html
For automated submission with ESR's freshmeat-submit script.
Only mention the program's base name in the error messages.
Revision 1.6 completely broke PI processing, so back that out for now.

Put the options list in some kind of order, and make the error messages
have a consistent format.
Don't put a "v" before the version number here.

TODO items are nowadays listed at SourceForge; this file doesn't serve a
purpose anymore.
Also remove the hidden files from the debian directory.

The debian directory no longer corresponds to the actual Debian package, so
it would only be confusing to keep it around.

Bug #1052834 (PIs in dsssl/doc sources causing jade errors)

apparently jade has a problem dealing with single quotation marks
in PIs -- at least it appears like that in the case where it needs
to take a single-quoted value from within a PI and use it to write
a filename; so changed al single-quote filenames in PIs to doubly
quoted ones; seems to have made jade happy

Give othercredit some useful rendering in print output, by copying over the
author rendering.  Fix author-list-string for authorgroups that contain
both authors and othercredits.  (bug #1038081)
